The '''Newcastle Personality Assessor (NPA)''' is a [[personality test]] designed to measure the test-taker's [[personality type|personality]] on five dimensions: [[Extroversion]], [[Neuroticism]], [[Conscientious]], [[Agreeableness]], and [[Openness]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Daniel Nettle |url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2009/mar/07/personality-test |title=Personality test: How neurotic or extrovert are you? &#124; Life and style |publisher=The Guardian |date= 2009-03-07|accessdate=2012-10-05 |location=London}}</ref> The 10-questions assessor was developed by [[Daniel Nettle]], a [[behavioral scientist]] at the [[Centre for Behaviour & Evolution]], [[Newcastle University]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.staff.ncl.ac.uk/daniel.nettle/ |title=Daniel Nettle's personal web page |publisher=Staff.ncl.ac.uk |date= |accessdate=2012-10-05}}</ref>

